By IFEOMA AKA ENUGU- An APC chieftain, Mrs Adaku Ogbu, has emerged the Enugu East senatorial candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Enugu State.The emergence of Ogbu on Saturday in Enugu followed the successful senatorial primary election organised by the party’s Electoral Committee, led by Mrs Abigail Igwe.Ogbu polled 270 votes out of the 284 votes cast during the exercise, monitored by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC).In his acceptance speech, Ogbu appreciated the party delegates for their support, noting that it is a good start.Ogbu, who hails from Nkanu East Local Government Area, said if voted in the general election, her administration would work towards turning things around in the zone.She promised to liaise with the executive to attract infrastructure that would benefit her people.Ogbu, who was also APC aspirant in 2019 primaries, stressed that all indigenes and other residents in the zone would be carried along in the scheme of things, if she is elected.In the same vein, the APC electoral committee Chairman, Igwe, commended the party’s delegates for conducting themselves in good manner during the exercise. (NAN) Enugu - Prince Lawrence Eze, the embattled All Progressives Congress (APC) Senatorial Candidate for Enugu East says he has appealed the judgement nullifying his candidature by a Federal High Court, Enugu. Eze told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in a telephone interview in Enugu on Tuesday that he had… In "Politics" By ALEX ENEBELI Enugu- Ahead of the primary elections of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), the statutory and ad hoc delegates from Enugu West Senatorial District on Sunday assured Gov. Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi of Enugu Stateof maximum support. •Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi They said they were solidly behind him, and would vote… In "Politics" By EMMANUEL ACHA/BENSON EZEUGWU Chief Ike Ekweremadu ENUGU- Former Deputy President of the Senate, Chief Ike Ekweremadu has announced his withdrawal from the Peoples Democra